[[File:131012 Tokachigawa Onsen Otofuke Hokkaido Japan09bs.jpg|thumb|250px|[[北海道遺産]]のモール温泉]]
'''Tokachigawa Onsen''' (十勝川温泉) is a {{ill|hot spring|ja|温泉|1=Onsen|1=Onsen|qq=draft|qq=draft}} located in {{ill|Otofuke, Hokkaido|ja|音曲町|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Kato District, Hokkaido|ja|河東郡|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, Japan.
== Spring Quality (Onsen Properties) == The onsen's spring quality includes sodium chloride ({{ill|Chloride Spring|ja|塩化物泉|1=Brine spring|1=Brine spring|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) and {{ill|bicarbonate spring|ja|炭酸水素塩泉|1=Bicarbonate springs|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, classified as weakly alkaline, hypotonic, and high-temperature.
Millions of years ago, the {{ill|Tokachi Plain|ja|十勝平野|qq=draft|qq=draft}} was a vast inland bay surrounded by wetlands where peat accumulated. This peat transformed into lignite over time, and the onsen water emerges from strata deep underground containing lignite deposits. Tokachigawa Onsen has a unique feature of being a {{ill|moor hot spring|ja|モール温泉|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, rich in organic matter derived from plants.
== Hot Spring Town == Located along the {{ill|Tokachi River|ja|十勝川|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and {{ill|Hokkaido Route 73|ja|北海道道現73号線|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, the hot spring town features several facilities, including {{ill|Michi-no-Eki Garden Spa Tokachigawa Onsen|ja|道の駅ガーデンスパ十勝川温泉|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.{{Cite web|url=http://www.tokachigawa.jp |title=道の駅ガーデンスパ十勝川温泉 |accessdate=2020-10-23}} Other attractions include footbaths and year-round outdoor activities organized by the Tokachi Nature Center.{{Cite web|url=http://www.nature-tokachi.co.jp |title=十勝ネイチャーセンター |accessdate=2015-06-15}}
== History == The onsen's historical record dates back to 1874 when it was mentioned in "Hokkaido Chishi Youryo" as "Otogawa Yu." Initially utilized by local Ainu people as "medicine water," the modern history of Tokachigawa Onsen began in 1900 when Kahei Iba redirected lukewarm water into a wooden box for communal use. By 1913, Touzaburo Maeda developed the area, discovering higher-temperature springs through digging efforts.{{Cite web|url=http://www.sasaihotel.com/gensen/ |title=筋温泉物語 |work=Hotel Sasai |accessdate=2015-06-15}}
== Events ==
Tokachigawa Swan Festival "Sairinka" (Late January - Late February)
Footpath Walking Event (June)
Flower Landscape "Hanack and Flower Road" (Late June - Late July)
Autumn Festa in Tokachigawa (Early October - Early November)
== Access ==
JR {{ill|Nemuro Main Line|ja|根室本線|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, Obihiro Station, 20 minutes by car.{{Cite web|url=http://www.tokachigawa.net/access/ |title=アクセス |publisher=Tokachigawa Onsen Tourism Association |accessdate=2015-06-15}}
From Tokachigawa IC (Dōto Expressway), 25 minutes by car.
